node.text:
To conclude the year, this week on #TheHYPEreport @thecamp0ut and our Footwear Editors discuss the best sneakers of 2019 as well as the most important sneakers of the decade. From 2019 standouts like sacai x Nike’s LDWaffle and CPFM’s Vapormax to shoes of the decade like the adidas YEEZY BOOST and fragment design’s Air Jordan 1, our editors discuss it all.⁠
-⁠
Link in bio. Thank you for tuning in and don’t forget to subscribe to #TheHYPEreport on wherever you get your podcasts.

After introducing his first shoe with @adidasoriginals, @blondey is now providing an alternate colorway of the Superstar. Limited to 200 pairs, the alternate take is centered around a transparent black-tinged polyurethane upper accented by matching three-stripes panels and black leather on the tongue, ankle collar and lace panels.⁠⠀
Photo: Thames

@nike is now providing a new vibrant colorway for its more modern weatherproof outdoor model, the Air Max 720 Horizon. The upper is built with fully blacked-out GORE-TEX and synthetic materials, providing a water-resistant and insulating canvas with a “University Red” overlay wrapped around. The shoe is available now for $240 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

What was your favorite sneaker release of 2019?⁠
Comment below 👇⁠
Photo: @cran⁠
-⁠
Tag us in your photos or videos to be featured.⁠ #hypebeastkicks

@converse_jp is offering a playful twist on the classic Chuck Taylor All Star 100 featuring a logo that’s been sliced and repositioned. Find the shoe in black and white colorways made with eco-friendly TENCEL fabrics. The shoe is currently available at Converse Japan’s website for $75 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Converse Japan

For its 30th anniversary, Japanese sneaker brand @asics is re-releasing its highly popular GEL-Lyte III model in a classic, vivid colorway. Expect the shoe to arrive January 1for approx. $135 USD.⁠
Photo: @43einhalb

@alexandermcqueen is the latest luxury brand to provide its take on transparent air bubble-infused soles with the release of these leather low-top sneakers featuring the striking design detail.⁠⠀
Photo: @modaoperandi

After being unveiled at @virgilaboh's “Figures of Speech” exhibition at the MCA Chicago, we are now learning that the @off____white x @jumpman23 “Canary Yellow” is rumored for a release. See more of the rumored release by visiting the link in bio.⁠
Photo: Mca Chicago

@nike's iconic Air Force 1 LV8 has been given a deconstructed update, showcasing a host of new elements such as a translucent Swoosh and debossed detailing all around. Other features include suede and off-white details and a translucent gum outsole. Expect the shoe to release in the coming weeks for $144 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: @noir.fonce

Luxury consignment retailer @therealreal recently put together data that ranks the top nine sneakers with the highest resale values over the past year with @nike dominating the list, contributing eight out of nine pairs. See which shoe models made the list by clicking the link in bio.⁠
Photo: Nike

@newbalance has looked to @beams_official and @mitasneakers for an MT580 collaboration adorned in GORE-TEX. The most notable addition to the sneaker is a protective zipped lace guard on the tongue, adding to the minimalist-meets-militant offering. Find the shoe on Mita Sneakers' website for approx. $165 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Mita Sneakers

Footwear festivities 👟🎄⁠
Photo: @kikiblini⁠
-⁠
Tag us in your photos or videos to be featured.⁠ #hypebeastkicks

It’s been a storied tradition for @nba players to break out their best kicks on Christmas Day. We put together what we believe are the best game day Christmas sneakers of the decade. Tell us your thoughts and let us know who do you think will have the best kicks on the court tomorrow. 
Music: @blaaqgold

@maisonmargiela's new Spring/Summer 2020 Replica Super Bounce Sneaker features a cream and grey upper atop a transparent bulbous sole. Find the unique pair in February for $760 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: LN-CC

@nike is aiming to reduce material waste with the new Atsume silhouette. A design that uses offcuts — pieces of material that are normally discarded when a pattern is cut — as part of its layered look, the Atsuma is an exercise in sustainability and the use of negative space alike. Read more about the design by visiting the link in bio and expect the shoe to arrive online January 1.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@maisonmargiela have dressed the Cross Derby and Cross Loafer silhouettes in eye-catching colorways. The two shoes fuse elements of formal dress shoes with trainers, as their classic uppers sit atop an oversized, ridged sole unit. Both pairs are available now from @ssense, priced at $1355 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: SSENSE

@newbalance has prepared Kawhi Leonard's popular OMN1S in a new "Money Stacks" colorway. Drawing from the almighty dollar, the latest style of Kawhi's signature shoe features a mix of green, grey, and tan tones atop its woven upper. Similarly, the tan midfoot strap is a nod to the rubber bands that often encircle giant stacks of cash. Expect its arrival online and at select retailers on December 26 for $140 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: New Balance

@rickowensonline has dropped a new bondage-inspired Maximal Runner silhouette in a light cream-colored beige palette. Coming in a mix of leather, suede, rubber, and cotton, the shoe's upper features tightly layered laces that cover the forefoot. Find the shoe on @thelncc's website for around $1,000 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: LN-CC

@cncpts have officially revealed its @nike Kyrie 6 collaborations with the "Khepri" and a kids-only "Golden-Gummy", each continuing the duo's Ancient Egyptian theme. ⁠⠀
Photo: Concepts

@nike has introduced the most influential elements from the Air Max 90 to a new slip-on sandal in "Black/White", "Smoke Grey/Volt", and "White/Rose" colorways. Find Air Max unit-equipped slides on Nike's webstore for an MSRP of $75 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@obj's @nike Vapor Untouchable Pro 3 OBJ Uptempo Cleats are receiving the holiday treatment with a Christmas themed shoe that pays homage to the Grinch.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@vans is bringing back its psychedelic “Refract Pack” for the iconic Sk8-Hi. Offered in two colorways, the shoe comes with a blacked-out upper as a canvas for a burst of vivid and colorful stripes running along the laterals. The black-soled silhouette brings out warmer tones ranging from reds to oranges to purples, while the white-soled iteration boasts colors from all across the rainbow’s spectrum. Both pairs are available now on Vans’ website for $65 each.⁠⠀
Photo: Vans

@nike and @obj are coming together for an Air Max 720 collaboration inspired by the richly-detailed backgrounds we come across in the “natural world.” The “Canyon Gold/Hyper Grape” iteration features a vibrant orange, mild gray, and straightforward white colorway with purple lacing and a translucent sole. Expect the sneaker to release on December 28 on Nike’s website for $200 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@nike’s Air Ghost Racer has now surfaced in “Mineral Teal.” Constructed of two different white meshes, the sneaker features a range of overlays from nubuck to leather to synthetic plastics that are mostly dressed in black. “Photo Blue” hints are also apparent on the midfoot Swoosh, heel, and sockliner which work to contrast against the pops of “Mineral Teal” on the midfoot, forefoot, tongue, and heel. Cop a pair now on Nike’s website for $130 USD.⁠⠀
Photo: Nike

@kswiss has teamed up with ‘The Matrix’ to honor of the iconic film’s 20th anniversary. Dubbed “The Matrix Code,” the footwear capsule includes a special edition of the K-slide and the Classic 2000 all with motifs inspired by the visuals of the movie. The slides are constructed with a padded rubber sole and EVA upper highlighting the Matrix’s digital rain graphics whereas the Classic 2000 is comprised of black leather featuring debossed designs of binary code and glitchy green accents. Look for both styles to release at K-Swiss’ website and other retailers on December 31.⁠⠀
Photo: K-Swiss
